description.plain:
Kyrre Gørvell-Dahll (born on September 11, 1991), better known by his stage name, Kygo, is a Norwegian DJ and record producer born in Singapore. He grew up in Bergen, Vestland.

A remix of Ed Sheeran’s “I See Fire” started his career, but he’s mostly known for his hits “Firestone” with Conrad Sewell and “Stole the Show” with Parson James. At the end of 2015, Kygo released his third hit-single “Stay” featuring Maty Noyes.

On 13 May 2016, Kygo released his debut studio album Cloud Nine with less popular tracks like “Raging” featuring Kodaline and “Carry Me” featuring Julia Michaels

He went on making more tracks and released “It Ain’t Me” with vocals from Selena Gomez being the first single of his sophomore album. This song peaked on the charts for months.

description.plain:
“It Ain’t Me” is an uptempo tropical house breakup song. It features Selena Gomez on vocals. In the song, Selena breaks up with someone by asking who will take care of him—when that person isn’t her. Actor Vin Diesel is mistakenly credited as a background vocalist, when what he actually did was an in-studio cover version of the track with Kygo himself in the booth; adding several ad-libs during the beatdrops.

The track is the first single from the second studio album by Norwegian EDM producer Kygo. The song was released on Kygo’s official Vevo, after previews on Selena’s Instagram.

https://www.instagram.com/p/BQdk0XEAqLJ/?taken-by=selenagomez

songs.full_title: Stole the Show by Kygo (Ft. Parson James)
songs.title: Stole the Show

description.plain:
“Stole the Show” is a single from Kygo’s debut album. It uses a show at a theatre as a metaphor for a great relationship ending.

Vocalist Parson James wrote the original version of the song. He described the concept in an interview with V:

Everyone was begging me to write a ballad, and I was not trying to write one because I didn’t think I had been in love before… it was about this guy that I was not in a relationship with, and pretended like we were. We would just be with each other when it was convenient. “Stole the Show” is sort of that thing like, Okay, we don’t hate each other, it’s fine, but this is going nowhere. We’ve put on a good act, but I think it’s time for us to close the curtains.

When Kygo’s manager played him the track, he loved it and reached out to James via social media. According to James in an interview with Billboard, he was reluctant to collaborate because he “was so attached to the song.” He then said that after listening to Kygo’s remix of Martin Gaye’s Sexual Healing, he “fell in love with what he [kygo] was doing.”
Kygo gave the track a tropical house treatment and it became a major success for himself and James, who was soon signed to RCA due in part to the success of this song. He re-released the original version of the song later that year.



On March 23rd, the music video debuted for the YouTube Music Awards 2015. It features two aliens reuniting with each other at a party as the government comes after them.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BgfcToAjfdc

songs.full_title: Stargazing by Kygo (Ft. Justin Jesso)
songs.title: Stargazing

description.plain:
“Stargazing” is about a son’s love for his father who died when he was just a child. As seen in the music video, the son then find ways to assemble a rocket to “look” for his dead father in the sky of a million stars. He was determined to do so because his father wrote him that he could always “find” him in the stars.

This song was released on 21 September 2017. Almost three months later, an orchestral version of the song was released.
